-- Thailand Set to Reduce Rice-Support Price by 20%
-- B y   S u p u n n a b u l   S u w a n n a k i j
-- 2013-06-19T04:25:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-19/thailand-set-to-reduce-rice-support-price-by-20-correct-.html
(Corrects purchase limit to baht per family.)  Thailand National Rice Policy
Committee approves 20% reduction to 12,000 baht/t in farmer
support prices for white rice, Commerce Minister Boonsong
Teriyapirom tells reporters. 
* Price cut effective from July 1 for second harvest of 2012-2013
* Rice committee will study possible price cut for 2013-2014 
* Rice-price cut still needs approval from cabinet 
* Purchases from second harvest limited to 500,000 baht per
family from June 20. 
* Thailand cuts price to reduce spending and rein in  budget
deficit   To contact the reporter on this story:
Supunnabul Suwannakij in Bangkok at 
